==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hard-boiled
<hw>hard-boiled</hw></mhw> <pos>adj.</pos>
<def>not given to sentimentality or gentleness; -- of people; <as>as, a
<ex>hard-bitten</ex> character</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pugnacious, tough.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hardboard</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: hard-boiled
<hw>hard-boiled</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>same as
<er>hard-bitten</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hard-bitten, pugnacious.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>emotionally hardened; -- used of persons.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> callous, case-hardened, hardened.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>cooked until the yolk is solid; -- used of eggs;
<as>as, a breakfast of pancakes and <ex>hard-boiled</ex>
eggs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hardbound</ent>⟦br⟧
